Reasoning: The paper focuses on investigating the challenges faced by users with no experience in designing graphical user interfaces and proposes a GUI prototyping assistance tool called GUIComp that provides real-time, multi-faceted feedback on a user's current design. This paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI) category as it deals with designing user interfaces and improving the user experience. It could also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category as it proposes a tool to assist in the software development process. Additionally, it could be categorized under Computer Communications (cs.CC) as it deals with the communication between the user and the software. It could also be categorized under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it involves online workers assessing the created GUIs. Finally, it could be categorized under User Experience (cs.UE) as it aims to improve the user experience during the design process.
